key.name: Warning line 3
key.value: In the Commodity Balances as well as in Food Balance Sheet, negative imbalances can occur because of rounding errors, trade imbalances, multiple inputs or non conventional input into a processed item. While these cases are rare, it should be considered as "statistical discrepancy". In the new version of our data base (FAOSTAT2), this problem is being addressed.

In the Commodity Balances as well as in Food Balance Sheet, negative imbalances can occur because of rounding errors, trade imbalances, multiple inputs or non conventional input into a processed item. While these cases are rare, it should be considered as "statistical discrepancy". In the new version of our data base (FAOSTAT2), this problem is being addressed.

Dans les Bilans de produits et Bilans alimentaires, des déséquilibres de bilans peuvent subsister à cause des erreurs d'arrondis, des déséquilibres de balance commerciale, multiples inputs ou inputs non conventionnels des produits transformés. Bien que ces cas soient rares, ils devraient être considérés comme des "incohérences statistiques". Dans la nouvelles version de notre base de données (FAOSTAT2), on est entrain de re-étudier ce problème.

En la materia Balance de Productos así como en la Hoja de Balance de Alimentos, los desequilibrios negativos pueden ocurrir a causa de errores de redondeo, los desequilibrios del comercio, múltiples entradas o la entrada no convencional en un artículo procesado. Aunque estos casos son raros y se deben considerar como discrepancia estadística. En la versión nueva de nuestra base de datos (FAOSTAT2), este problema será reconsiderado más cuidadosamente.

In the Commodity Balances as well as in Food Balance Sheet, negative imbalances can occur because of rounding errors, trade imbalances, multiple inputs or non conventional input into a processed item. While these cases are rare, it should be considered as "statistical discrepancy". In the new version of our data base (FAOSTAT2), this problem is being addressed.

In the Commodity Balances as well as in Food Balance Sheet, negative imbalances can occur because of rounding errors, trade imbalances, multiple inputs or non conventional input into a processed item. While these cases are rare, it should be considered as "statistical discrepancy". In the new version of our data base (FAOSTAT2), this problem is being addressed.
